<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1893-01-19T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1893-01-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="427" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d427">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Foster</persName> to Señor
                                    <persName type="to">Cayetano Romero</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1893-01-19"><hi rend="italic">January 19,
                                1893</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the
                            receipt of your notes of 12th instant and to say that I have
                            communicated to the Secretary of War the suggestion that the U. S.
                            Government station troops at the fords of the Rio Grande between Rio
                            Grande City and Laredo, and also the statement which you send me
                            relative to the Mexican forces now on the right bank of that river.</p>
                        <p>Accept, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">John W. Foster.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>